answerText: Rabin-Karp algorithm[10] The Rabin-Karp algorithm is generally inferior to the Boyer-Moore algorithm; both accomplish this task, which typically involves finding a target inside some text.

question: Question: It gets around the problem of computing on subsets by picking a rolling hash that involves a modulo operation on a large prime.  [10] Identify this doubly-eponymous algorithm, which runs in big-O of n time, where n is the length of the input.
